250 g Ground Chicken
113 g Spring Mix
1 unit(s) Ciabatta Roll
113 g Baby Tomatoes
1 unit(s) Mini Cucumber
7 g Chives
0.17 cup Panko Breadcrumbs
2 tbsp Hot Sauce
3 tbsp Yogurt Sauce
1 tbsp White Wine Vinegar
1 unit(s) Honey
1 tbsp Zesty Garlic Blend
1 tbsp Unsalted Butter*
1.5 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Halve tomatoes.
Thinly slice cucumber.
Thinly slice chives.
Cut or tear ciabatta into 1/2-inch peices.
Add yogurt sauce and half the chives to a small bowl. Season with salt and pepper. Stir to combine.
Add vinegar, 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) sugar and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil to a large bowl. Stir to mix. This is your salad dressing.

Heat a medium non-stick pan (large pan for 4 ppl) over medium-high heat.
When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter. Swirl pan until melted, 30 sec. Add ciabatta. Cook stiring often until croutons are golden-brown and crispy. 4-5 min.
Remove from heat. Season with half the Zesty Garlic Blend, salt and pepper. Transfer croutons to another small bowl. Wipe out pan.

Add panko, chicken, half the hot sauce, remaining chives and remaining Zesty Garlic Blend to another large bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then combine.
Form mixture into 6 (12) 2-inch-wide patties.

Reheat the same pan over medium heat.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil then patties. Cook until golden brown, and cooked through, 2-3 min per side.**
Remove from heat. Drizzle honey and remaining hot sauce over patties. Flip to coat.

Add tomatoes, cucumber, spring mix and half hte croutons to bowl with dressing. Toss to coat.
Divide salad and patties between plates. Top salad with remaining croutons.
Dollop yogurt sauce over patties.

If you've opted to get chicken, prep and cook it in the same way the recipe instructs you to prep and cook the turkey.**